.TH "Navigator.getBattery" "JS" "July 26, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Navigator.getBattery \- Navigator: getBattery() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]getBattery()\f[B]\f[R] method provides information about
the system\[cq]s battery.
It returns a battery promise, which resolves with a
\f[CR]BatteryManager\f[R] object providing some properties to get the
battery status also some events you can handle to monitor the battery
status.
This implements the Battery Status API; see that documentation for
additional details, a guide to using the API, and sample code.
.PP
Since Chrome 103, the \f[CR]Navigator.getBattery()\f[R] method of
Battery Status API only expose to secure context.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] Access to this feature may be controlled by the
\f[CR]Permissions\-Policy\f[R] directive \f[CR]battery\f[R].
.RE
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getBattery()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]Promise\f[R] that fulfills with a \f[CR]BatteryManager\f[R]
object which you can use to get information about the battery\[cq]s
state.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]NotAllowedError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Use of this feature was blocked by a Permissions Policy.
.TP
\f[B]SecurityError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
The User Agent does not expose battery information to insecure contexts
and this method was called from an insecure context.
.SH EXAMPLES
This example fetches the current charging state of the battery and
establishes a handler for the \f[CR]chargingchange\f[R] event, so that
the charging state is recorded whenever it changes.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]let\f[R] batteryIsCharging = \f[B]false\f[R];

navigator.getBattery().then((battery) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  batteryIsCharging = battery.charging;

  battery.addEventListener(\[dq]chargingchange\[dq], () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    batteryIsCharging = battery.charging;
  });
});
.EE
.PP
For more examples and details, see Battery Status API.
